{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3488 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3488 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C3488","pos":[618,638]},{"content":"'var' is not allowed when the default capture mode is by-reference","pos":[639,705]},{"content":"When you specify that the default capture mode for a lambda expression is by-reference, you cannot pass a variable by reference to the capture clause of that expression.","pos":[712,881]},{"content":"To correct this error","pos":[891,912]},{"content":"Do not explicitly pass the variable to the capture clause, or","pos":[922,983]},{"content":"Do not specify by-reference as the default capture mode, or","pos":[993,1052]},{"content":"Specify by-value as the default capture mode, or","pos":[1062,1110]},{"content":"Pass the variable by value to the capture clause.","pos":[1120,1169]},{"content":"(This might change the behavior of the lambda expression.)","pos":[1170,1228]},{"content":"Example","pos":[1237,1244]},{"pos":[1248,1414],"content":"The following example generates C3488 because a reference to the variable <ph id=\"ph1\">`n`</ph> appears in the capture clause of a lambda expression whose default mode is by-reference:","source":"The following example generates C3488 because a reference to the variable `n` appears in the capture clause of a lambda expression whose default mode is by-reference:"},{"content":"Example","pos":[1536,1543]},{"content":"The following example shows four possible resolutions to C3488:","pos":[1547,1610]},{"content":"See Also","pos":[2170,2178]},{"content":"Lambda Expressions","pos":[2183,2201]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3488 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-csharp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3488\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3488\"\nms.assetid: 0a6fcd76-dd3b-48d7-abb3-22eccda96034\ncaps.latest.revision: 8\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\ntranslation.priority.mt: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3488\n'var' is not allowed when the default capture mode is by-reference  \n  \n When you specify that the default capture mode for a lambda expression is by-reference, you cannot pass a variable by reference to the capture clause of that expression.  \n  \n### To correct this error  \n  \n-   Do not explicitly pass the variable to the capture clause, or  \n  \n-   Do not specify by-reference as the default capture mode, or  \n  \n-   Specify by-value as the default capture mode, or  \n  \n-   Pass the variable by value to the capture clause. (This might change the behavior of the lambda expression.)  \n  \n## Example  \n The following example generates C3488 because a reference to the variable `n` appears in the capture clause of a lambda expression whose default mode is by-reference:  \n  \n```  \n// C3488a.cpp  \n  \nint main()  \n{  \n   int n = 5;  \n   [&, &n]() { return n; } (); // C3488  \n}  \n```  \n  \n## Example  \n The following example shows four possible resolutions to C3488:  \n  \n```  \n// C3488b.cpp  \n  \nint main()  \n{  \n   int n = 5;  \n  \n   // Possible resolution 1:  \n   // Do not explicitly pass &n to the capture clause.  \n   [&]() { return n; } ();  \n  \n   // Possible resolution 2:  \n   // Do not specify by-reference as the default capture mode.  \n   [&n]() { return n; } ();  \n  \n   // Possible resolution 3:  \n   // Specify by-value as the default capture mode.  \n   [=, &n]() { return n; } ();  \n  \n   // Possible resolution 4:  \n   // Pass n by value to the capture clause.  \n   [n]() { return n; } ();  \n}  \n```  \n  \n## See Also  \n [Lambda Expressions](../../cpp/lambda-expressions-in-cpp.md)"}